    <h1 class="hero-title">Real-Time Health System Command Layer</h1>
    <div class="hero-subtitle">Sovereign National Control Architecture for Live Visibility & Intelligent Orchestration</div>

    <img src="bp-18.png" alt="Real-Time Health System Command Layer" class="hero-image" />
</header>

<div class="container">

    <!-- Executive Summary -->
    <div class="card">
        <div class="section-title">Executive Summary</div>
        <p>
            This blueprint defines a sovereign real-time “Command Layer” enabling national visibility,  
            operational synchronization, and autonomous health system stabilization.  
            It functions as the live nervous system of a nation’s healthcare infrastructure,  
            aggregating signals from hospitals, logistics, workforce, finance, and crisis sensors  
            into an integrated operational intelligence platform.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Strategic Rationale -->
    <div class="card">
        <div class="section-title">Strategic Rationale</div>
        <p>
            Modern healthcare complexity exceeds human-manageable thresholds.  
            Decision latency, siloed data, and delayed intervention windows  
            create systemic fragility at national scale.  
            A real-time command layer eliminates these structural limitations  
            by enabling continuous monitoring, predictive alerts,  
            and automated orchestration of interdependent health subsystems.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- System Architecture -->
    <div class="card">
        <div class="section-title">System Architecture</div>

        <p><strong>1. Real-Time Signal Fusion Layer</strong> — Integrates clinical, operational, financial, IoT, and crisis data streams.</p>
        <p><strong>2. National Command Dashboard</strong> — Provides live system-wide visibility and intervention controls.</p>
        <p><strong>3. AI Decision Engine</strong> — Generates recommendations, predicts system failures, and automates micro-interventions.</p>
        <p><strong>4. Stabilization Protocol Layer</strong> — Executes autonomous corrective actions across institutions.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Use Cases -->
    <div class="card">
        <div class="section-title">Key Use Cases</div>
        <ul class="usecases">
            <li>Live national clinical load balancing</li>
            <li>Real-time workforce orchestration</li>
            <li>Supply chain stabilization</li>
            <li>Surge detection and automated response</li>
            <li>Cross-institution operational alignment</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

